                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14244093" author="blerer" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2014 13:04:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When the patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7111&quot; title=&quot;Include snippet of CQL query near error in SyntaxError messages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7111&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7111&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was made cassandra-2.1 was using ANTLR 3.2. and trunk was using the version 3.5.2. As mentionned in my &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7111?focusedCommentId=14063463&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-14063463&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;comment&lt;/a&gt; ANTLR 3.5.2 seems to produce sometime some invalid tokens. It is one of those invalid tokens that caused the &lt;tt&gt;ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
The problem appears now because we migrated ANTLR to version 3.5.2 without backporting the invalid token fix from trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14244179" author="blerer" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2014 14:28:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both patchs add error logging to QueryProcessor and a unit test to check the correct behaviour.&lt;br/&gt;
The patch for 2.1 back port the fix for the problem from trunk. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14244537" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2014 18:08:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed as 254d6f7e9c689c639f85f3f5119f4a812d295f05.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
